(Corrects currency in headline, first paragraph.)  RosVynil, a joint venture between
Sibur Holding and SolVin SA, signed a 750 million euro ($1
billion) loan today with lenders including the European Bank for
Reconstruction & Development to build a greenfield plant to
produce polyvinylchloride in  Nizhny Novgorod .  The companies released the information at a signing
ceremony in  St. Petersburg .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
